And for us humans we use the decimal number system 

10
00:00:39.730 --> 00:00:43.450
We express numbers in positional decimal format 

11
00:00:43.540 --> 00:00:46.570
But the computer can't store decimal numbers directly

12
00:00:46.610 --> 00:00:49.990
The computer can understand only binary number system 

13
00:00:50.420 --> 00:00:53.870
which is also called as the base 2 number system 

14
00:00:53.930 --> 00:00:58.340
So the computer automatically converts the decimal number to binary format before using it 

15
00:00:59.240 --> 00:01:00.860
Whatever be the data

16
00:01:01.470 --> 00:01:05.120
The computer always converts it into its only known language 

17
