So if we have a number in decimal system  

20
00:01:14.670 --> 00:01:16.950
how can we convert it into its binary format? 

21
00:01:17.790 --> 00:01:19.889
Let us understand it using an example 

22
00:01:20.040 --> 00:01:21.990
so we have the decimal number 22 

23
00:01:22.590 --> 00:01:26.920
To convert this into its binary, we have to divide the number by 2.

24
00:01:27.010 --> 00:01:30.909
It is because, the base of the binary number system is 2.

25
00:01:31.270 --> 00:01:35.190
Similarly if you need to convert a decimal number to it's octal number

26
00:01:35.760 --> 00:01:38.390
We have to divide it by it's base 8 

27
00:01:38.400 --> 00:01:41.310
and to convert a decimal number to it's hexa decimal number,

28
00:01:41.730 --> 00:01:44.390
We have to divide it by it's base 16 

29
00:01:44.610 --> 00:01:47.250
so that is the first step in decimal to binary conversion 

30
00:01:47.950 --> 00:01:52.550
Divide the number by two and write down the remainder of the division 

31
00:01:52.870 --> 00:01:55.390
So here 22 by 2 is equal to 11 

32
00:01:56.080 --> 00:01:58.210
and remainder is equal to zero 

33
00:01:58.500 --> 00:02:00.990
again divide the result 11 by 2 

34
00:02:01.230 --> 00:02:04.840
and we get the result five and remainder is equal to 1 

35
00:02:04.940 --> 00:02:05.880
so note it down 

36
00:02:06.280 --> 00:02:10.100
and this procedure should be continued until we get zero as the result

37
00:02:10.390 --> 00:02:12.230
 So here the result is five 

38
00:02:12.350 --> 00:02:15.760
So divide five by two and we get 2 as the result 

39
00:02:15.850 --> 00:02:17.890
and remainder equal to one 

40
