and remainder equal to zero 

42
00:02:22.910 --> 00:02:26.100
So divide one divided by two and we get the result zero

43
00:02:26.590 --> 00:02:28.510
 and remainder equal to one 

44
00:02:28.650 --> 00:02:31.790
So now the result equal to zero and we can stop 

45
00:02:31.790 --> 00:02:34.820
And to get the binary value of this number

46
00:02:34.820 --> 00:02:37.640
 just write the remainders of the operation in the reverse order 

47
00:02:37.770 --> 00:02:40.040
that is from bottom to up

48
00:02:40.130 --> 00:02:44.110
So we get 10110 

49
00:02:44.110 --> 00:02:47.910
So this is how we can get the binary value of any decimal number 

