 into its corresponding decimal value 

73
00:04:05.870 --> 00:04:07.020
How can we do that? 

74
00:04:07.240 --> 00:04:11.360
We know that a binary number will be a string of zeros and ones 

75
00:04:11.470 --> 00:04:12.780
see an example 

76
00:04:12.781 --> 00:04:15.670
We have a binary value 10110 

77
00:04:15.680 --> 00:04:20.120
We have an easy method to convert this into its decimal value 

78
00:04:20.120 --> 00:04:23.370
And for that first we need to count the positions 

80
00:04:23.440 --> 00:04:26.710
and we count the positions from right to left 

81
00:04:26.800 --> 00:04:29.430
So the position of 0 is zero,  

82
00:04:29.490 --> 00:04:32.850
1 is one, next 1 is two 

83
00:04:32.850 --> 00:04:36.360
And next 0 is three and final 1 is four 

84
00:04:36.530 --> 00:04:38.660
Now that we have got the positions, 

85
00:04:38.670 --> 00:04:43.830
multiply these values  with two raised to position number and find the sum 

86
00:04:43.830 --> 00:04:47.780
that is 1 x 2 raised to its position 4 

87
00:04:47.780 --> 00:04:51.350
+ 0 x 2 raised to its position 3  

88
00:04:51.360 --> 00:04:55.250
+ 1 x 2 raised to its position 2 

89
00:04:55.250 --> 00:04:58.710
+ 1 x 2 raised to its position 1 

90
00:04:58.710 --> 00:05:02.260
+ 0 x 2 raised to its position 0 

91
00:05:02.270 --> 00:05:07.860
 which is 16 + 0 + 4 + 2 + 0

92
00:05:07.900 --> 00:05:09.330
That is 22 

93
00:05:09.730 --> 00:05:14.340
So this is the decimal equivalent of binary 10110 

94
00:05:14.830 --> 00:05:19.930
So  what we did is take each value and multiply with 2 raised to its position

95
00:05:19.980 --> 00:05:22.430
 and find the sum and we will get the decimal value 

